encyclopedia.content: overload对我们来说可能比较熟悉，可以翻译为重载，它是指我们可以定义一些名称相同的方法，通过定义不同的输入参数来区分这些方法，然后再调用时，VM就会根据不同的参数样式，来选择合适的方法执行。

entry.def: If you overload something such as a vehicle, you put more things or people into it than it was designed to carry.

example.ex: Don't overload the boat or it will sink...
Large meals overload the digestive system.
example.tran: 吃得太饱会加重消化系统的负担。

entry.tran: 使负担过重；给予…过多的工作（或问题、信息等）
entry.def: To overload someone with work, problems, or information means to give them more work, problems, or information than they can cope with.

example.ex: ...an effective method that will not overload staff with yet more paperwork.
example.tran: 不会再以更多的文书工作加重员工负荷的有效办法

entry.tran: 使（电力系统）过载；使超过负荷
entry.def: If you overload an electrical system, you cause too much electricity to flow through it, and so damage it.

example.tran: 千万不要使电源插座过载。
